Step 1: Create the Virtual Environment
Run the creation command for your respective operating system:
Windows:
py -m venv .venv

macOS/Linux:
python3 -m venv .venv


Step 2: Activate the Environment
You must activate the environment before installing packages.
Windows (Command Prompt):
.venv\Scripts\activate.bat

Windows (PowerShell):
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

macOS/Linux (bash/zsh):
source .venv/bin/activate

macOS/Linux (fish):
source .venv/bin/activate.fish


Step 3: Install Dependencies
Install the required packages from requirements.txt:
pip install -r requirements.txt


Step 4: Initialize the Database
Run the setup script to initialize the SQLite database:
python3 database/setup_db.py


Step 5: Run the Flask Application
Start the Flask development server:
python3 app.py


